quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,53,"Say, \"My worshipers who have transgressed against themselves do not despair of God's mercy, for God forgives all sins. He is the Ever-Forgiving, the Mercy-Giver"
  39,54,Turn in repentance to your Lord and submit to Him before the punishment comes upon you and you cannot be helped
  39,55,"Follow the best teaching sent down to you from your Lord before the punishment comes upon you suddenly, when you are not expecting it"
  39,56,"so that a soul may not say, \" How sorry I am for having neglected my duty to God and having been among the mockers"
  39,57,"or say, \"Had God guided me, I would have been among those who are mindful of God"
  39,58,"or say, when it sees the punishment, \"If only I had another chance to be among those who do good"
  39,59,"[But God will reply] \"No! My verses did come to you, but you denied them, turned arrogant, and denied the truth"
  39,60,"On the Day of Resurrection you will see those who lied about God with their faces darkened [by grief and sorrow]. Is not Hell the proper place for the arrogant"
  39,61,"God will save those who were mindful of Him by the virtue of their successful choices; no harm will touch them, nor will they grieve"
  39,62,"God is the Creator of all things, and He is the Guardian over all things"
  39,63,"The keys of the heavens and the earth are His. Those who reject the verses of God, it is they who are the doomed"